thread.title: EastEnders reveals alternate death for Ronnie and Roxy on Snapchat
thread.title_full: EastEnders reveals alternate death for Ronnie and Roxy on Snapchat

title: EastEnders reveals alternate death for Ronnie and Roxy on Snapchat
text:
Ronnie and Roxy Mitchell drowned in a swimming pool after Ronnie's wedding in disturbing scenes. 
However, BBC's announcer teased that an alternate ending would be revealed on BBC One's Snapchat account after the episode. 
It took a long time – but finally, fans got a glimpse of another possible ending for the Mitchell sisters. 
BBC EXIT: Ronnie and Roxy died on tonight's episode 
BBC TWIST: Roxy may have died in a different way 
In a brief montage of dimly lit scenes, Roxy's body is seen lifeless on a pool table, with Ronnie and Jack discovering her. 
Ronnie is also seen sobbing on a hospital floor while her voice is heard saying: "She's dead." 
And as the newlyweds find Roxy face down on the pool table, Ronnie is heard shouting Jack's name. 
It is unclear how actress Samantha Womack would have made her exit if this ending had have made it onto TV. 
BBC WEDDING DAY BLUES: Ronnie was seen weeping in her wedding dress Eastenders Spoiler: Backstage at the wedding of Ronnie and Jack Sunday, 30th October 2016 Albert square turn out for the wedding of the year at a large country house to celebrate Ronnie and Jack's big day. 1 / 24 ISOIMAGES The wedding of Ronnie and Jack just before tragedy strikes. 
Both she and Rita Simons were written out of the show, with fans awaiting their exits for months. 
However, many viewers are peeved at how long they had to wait for the alternate ending on Snapchat. 
The BBC announcer promised the clip following the broadcasted episode at 8pm, but the clip didn't surface on BBC's Snapchat until 10pm. 
SNAPCHAT DELAYED: Fans were furious that the Snapchat reveal took two hours 
The alternate ending was preceded by a string of snaps showing cut-outs of EastEnders characters with speech bubbles – for example, Aunt Babe saying: "Everybody take your seats" and Dot Cotton saying "Oh no, oh dear". 
Fans, who had been checking their Snapchats constantly, were angry about the delay. 
One person tweeted: "Why such a delay in the alternative ending. Is dot cotton in charge of your snapchat account " 
And another commented: "Imagine if BBC 1 just did that so we added their snapchat and they gained followers I just want to see it." 
Well, if so, it worked. Related articles
